  "description": "Discovery 4 made canonical: Rule 90 (Sierpinski fractal) with filterRes=0.82 — Q of approximately 9.9. Each time the fractal automaton updates cells 0–3, the filter cutoff sweeps, causing the resonant peak to briefly ring at a new frequency. The Sierpinski triangle's fractal structure in the filter domain produces fractal-like melodic overtones — audible pitch-like tones at the resonant frequency. Scope=4 for crisp, unsmoothed fractal steps. This is the engine's most melodically active state without playing a melody.",
